Novatek, Norilsk Nickel, Uralkali: Russian Equities Preview

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-08-11T20:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/novatek-norilsk-nickel-uralkali-russian-equities-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 0.5 percent to 1,438.91
yesterday. The dollar-denominated RTS Index added 0.5 percent to
1,544.83, rising for the first time in eight days.  OAO Novatek (NOTK RX):  Russia ’s largest private natural-gas
producer is scheduled to report financial results for the second
quarter today. Novatek shares advanced 3.5 percent to 368.34
rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): Russia will link the
export duty on copper to the market price of the metal,
according to an e-mailed statement from the government press
service late yesterday. Norilsk, Russia’s second-largest copper
producer by output in 2010, fell 1.9 percent to 6,480 rubles.  OAO Uralkali (URKA RX): Belarusian Potash Corp., a trading
arm of Uralkali, will supply 400,000 metric tons of potash to
 India  at $490 a ton from September to March, after the sale of
1.2 million tons last week at the same price, market researcher
FMB said in a note yesterday, which was confirmed by the
company. Uralkali shares rose 1.2 percent to 250.91 rubles.  To contact the reporters on this story:
